        "text_HFqXYG": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Professor of Marketing at Emory University’s Goizueta Business School.<br/>Holds a B.A. in mathematics, M.A. in statistics, and Ph.D. in marketing from the<br/>University of Pennsylvania. Author of Social Media Intelligence and Profiting from the<br/>Data Economy.<br/>Research focuses on customer relationship management, social media analytics, and<br/>the development of statistical models to understand customer behavior and support<br/>managerial decision-making. Work examines how technology and data shape<br/>interactions between consumers and firms.<br/>Publications appear in leading journals including Journal of Marketing, Journal of<br/>Marketing Research, Marketing Science, and Management Science, and have<br/>received multiple academic awards and recognitions</p>",
